Quetzalcoatl, also known as Kukulcan and Ehecatl, is the Feathered Serpent, god of the wind, god of arts and metallurgy, god of wisdom, and protector of the Second Sun. He is the least warlike of the Aztec gods.
He appears in the form of a couatl or a bewildering number of other monstrous forms, including that of a dragon. He is similar to Qotal. His archenemy is Tezcatlipoca.
His divine Realm is on the planet Venus, in the solar system of a parallel Earth. 

